                                                Hampi was the capital of the Vijayanagara Empire in the 14th century.By 1500CE, Hampi was the world's
                                                second-largest medieval-era city after Beijing.
                                            <br>
                                            Vijayanagara Empire was defeated by a coalition of Muslim sultanates; its capital was conquered,
                                            pillaged and destroyed in 1565, after which Hampi remained in ruins.
                                          <br>
                                          Hampi includes 1600 surviving remains of the last great Hindu kingdom in South India that include forts,
                                          sacred complexes, temples, shrines, halls, memorial and water structures etc.
                                        <br>
                                        The main focus in the Hampi includes <b>The Stone chariot</b> , <b>Virupaksha temple</b>, <b>Krishna
                                            temple</b>
                                      <br>
                                      <b>Vitthala temple</b> , <b>Hazara Rama temple</b> etc.
                                      <b>                Ruins of hampi has one of world's best ancient architecture which includes Jain temples, muslim temples,
                                        water complexes etc.
                                
                  <br>         Golden temple has been nominated as a UNESCO World Heritage Site.
         
      <br>
      A standout amongst the most appealing structures is the Vittala Temple . This temple has 56 melodic
      columns or the musical pillars. All 56 columns produce different sound when struck gently so they create
      music if used correctly.
